HIV/AIDS: Ƙaruwar sabbin kamuwa da cutar a China da kashi 14
China ta ba da rahoton cewa adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya ƙaru da kashi 14 cikin ɗari.
Hukumomin kiwon lafiya sun ce cutar ta shafi rayukan mutane fiye da 820,000 a kasar.
An samu sabbin mutane kusan 40 000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Mafi yawan sababbin cututtuka suna yaduwa ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke nuna canji a cikin ƙididdigar da aka yi a baya.
A wasu sassa na ƙasar Sin, HIV ya yi saurin yaduwa ta hanyar ƙarin jini.
Amma, a cewar jami'an kiwon lafiya na ƙasar Sin da suka halarci taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan, an rage yawan kamuwa da cutar HIV da aka yi ta wannan hanyar zuwa kusan babu.
Amma, shekara guda bayan haka, adadin mutane da suka kamu da cutar HIV da kuma AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma an ce nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Bincike ya nuna cewa saboda tsattsauran ra'ayi na kasar, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza suna aure da mata.
Yawancin cututtuka na cututtuka suna faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya a cikin irin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun daga shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin HIV ga kowa a matsayin wani sashe na kokarin magance matsalar.
